			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">never-obsolete wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">IRQBRK:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;sei<br />&nbsp; &nbsp;rti<br /></div><br /></div>
<br />
<br />That will deadlock your program.
<br />
<br />1)  I is already set by the IRQ.  The SEI does nothing.
<br />2)  RTI will pull status from the stack, resulting in I being cleared again
<br />3)  Because RTI will clear I, another IRQ will occur immediately, causing a deadlock in the IRQ handler.
<br />
<br />You need to acknowledge the IRQ.  I forget how this is done on the DMC.  I think you just read $4015, but you'll have to double-check.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

